content: I'm actually interested in trying out the breakfast burrito idea, but I was wondering if you could suggest some alternatives to black beans. I've had them before and they're okay, but I want to mix it up a bit. Also, do you think roasted sweet potatoes would work well in a breakfast burrito? I've had great success roasting them in the oven and they're so delicious with scrambled eggs, like in that dish I made on the morning of April 10th.
